# Database and API Guidelines

## Database Schema Guidelines
- Use clear and consistent naming for tables and columns
- Include proper indexes for frequently queried fields
- Store language content with proper character encoding
- Implement proper relations between learning materials
- Use appropriate field types for language-specific content

## API Endpoint Structure
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Use proper HTTP methods
- Implement proper error handling
- Include appropriate validation
- Document all endpoints

## Data Models
- Define clear Prisma models
- Use appropriate field types
- Implement proper relationships
- Include necessary indexes
- Add helpful comments

## Security
- Implement proper authentication
- Validate all user inputs
- Sanitize language content
- Use appropriate rate limiting
- Follow OWASP security guidelines

## Error Handling
- Use consistent error formats
- Include appropriate status codes
- Provide helpful error messages
- Log errors appropriately
- Handle language-specific errors

## Performance
- Optimize database queries
- Implement proper caching
- Use appropriate batch operations
- Monitor query performance
- Handle large datasets efficiently
